description: From Latin intricatus, past participle of intricare.

adjectives.description: intricate (comparative more intricate, superlative most intricate)

entries.meaning: Having a great deal of fine detail or complexity.
examples: The architecture of this clock is very intricate.

description: As the adjective; or by analogy with extricate.

verbs.description: intricate (third-person singular simple present intricates, present participle intricating, simple past and past participle intricated)
